items.badge_description: It’s been a long week and you deserve a drink, or five. Besides, isn’t that what your check is for?
Are you crazy? Five different types of beer in one day? Hope you were just sampling.

Looking for more kick than a session beer, but want to be able to stay for a few rounds? You have to keep it in the middle. That's 5 beers with an ABV greater than 5% and less than 10%. Try 5 more for Level 2!
We believe in IPA and you should too. You certainly have a taste for the hops! That's 5 different IPAs. Try 5 more for Level 2!

items.checkin_comment: Pretty good. A bit of sediment in the glass but still a good beer

items.badge_description: It takes the perfect amount of light, the right framing and a touch of creative love to get the perfect picture of your brew. Now it’s time to drink it! That’s 235 check-ins with a photo.

Canning is all the rage and it's not hard to see why - travels well, more environmentally friendly, and no need to carry your bottle opener. That's 30 checkins with the serving style of Can. Try 5 more for Level 7!

You may not be able to see through the haze, but that juicy, hoppy goodness goes down smooth. What started as a trend is here to stay. That's 15 different beers with the style of IPA - New England (Imperial or Single), Pale Ale - New England or IPA - Milkshake. Try 5 more for Level 4!

items.checkin_comment: Another top brew! Packs a flavor punch like an MP-5 and at 6.5% is easy to enjoy over time. Perfect accompaniment to the annual Die Hard viewing
